# #8 Java I/O (Input/Output )

### FileReader, FileWriter, BufferedReader, BufferedWriter, FileInputStream, FileOutputStream

- I/O streams

    Input - from source to application in order to read

    Output - from app to destination in order to write

- Byte and Character stream

    In java streams devide  two categories:

    Byte streams: Read byte-byte, suitable for all types of files(images, videos, text). Main classes
     are `InputStream` v…ô `OutputStream`.

    Character streams: Read symbol-symbol(16-bit Unicode), only for text files. Main classes are `Reader`
     and `Writer` .

- import `java.io.File`

    to perform various operations(methods) on files or folders